      <notesStmt>
        <note>Manuscript leaves.</note>
        <note>Title supplied by cataloger.</note>
        <note>Decoration : Two simple paintings in opaque watercolor. Each painting is of a person in pink garb on a green, hilly background with blue sky. One person is bald, standing, wearing sandals, a green cloak and a rope belt with two objects hanging from it holding a staff. The other is wearing a brown cloak and shoes and a white turban with a feather in it, holding a finger bowl and is seated next to a flask.</note>
        <note>Two unrelated manuscripts previously housed with this item have been separately cataloged as MS Or 152a and MS Or 152c.</note>
